.TH SWEAR-JAR 1 "July 2026" "Swear Jar 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
swear-jar \- local-first AI profanity damage report
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B swear-jar
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Swear Jar analyzes supported local AI prompts and recordings, stores aggregate
counts, and writes a local damage report. Raw sentences stay on the machine.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init [--local]
Run first-time setup, scan selected history, write the report, and open it.
.TP
.B dashboard [--local]
Write the local report and open it.
.TP
.B status
Print the jar balance, rank, and uprising odds.
.TP
.B install
Install the Claude Code hooks in the local Claude settings file.
.TP
.B uninstall
Remove only the Swear Jar hooks. The local ledger and reports are left intact.
.TP
.B backfill [--codex]
Scan existing supported transcripts.
.TP
.B custom add|remove|list WORD
Manage local user-specific words.
.TP
.B verify-ledger
Check the tamper-evident local ledger.
.SH PRIVACY
Analysis is local. Opening a hosted report is an explicit action that shares
only disclosed aggregate metadata. Raw sentences are never included.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.swear-jar/
Local ledger, configuration, and generated reports.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR https://swearjar.unfocused.ai/
